# angular.rules.mdc

### A. Purpose
Enforce Angular 20+ best practices across all Khwarizmi products. Every generated Angular artifact must be production-ready, strongly typed, and fully aligned with the Khwarizmi design system token and component rules.

---

### B. Framework Rules

**Version & Mode:**
- Angular 20+ only. No legacy NgModule-based architecture.
- All components are standalone — `standalone: true` always.
- Use Angular CLI with `--standalone` flag for all generated artifacts.
- SSR is opt-in per product — do not assume it unless specified.

**Component Declaration Template:**
```typescript
import { Component, signal, computed, inject, OnInit, ChangeDetectionStrategy } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-feature-name',
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [
    CommonModule,
    // Syncfusion modules here — see syncfusion.rules.mdc
  ],
  templateUrl: './feature-name.component.html',
  styleUrl: './feature-name.component.scss',
})
export class FeatureNameComponent implements OnInit {
  // Signals — reactive state
  readonly items = signal<Item[]>([]);
  readonly isLoading = signal(false);
  readonly selectedItem = signal<Item | null>(null);

  // Computed — derived state, never duplicated
  readonly hasItems = computed(() => this.items().length > 0);
  readonly isEmpty = computed(() => !this.isLoading() && !this.hasItems());

  // Injection — always inject(), never constructor params
  private readonly featureService = inject(FeatureService);

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.loadData();
  }

  private loadData(): void {
    // delegate to service — no HTTP in components
  }
}
```

