### E. Template Rules

**Control Flow — always use new Angular 17+ syntax:**
```html
<!-- ✅ New syntax -->
@if (isLoading()) {
  <ejs-skeleton height="200px" />
} @else if (isEmpty()) {
  <app-empty-state />
} @else {
  <ejs-grid [dataSource]="items()" />
}

@for (item of items(); track item.id) {
  <app-item-card [item]="item" (select)="onItemSelect($event)" />
}

@switch (userRole()) {
  @case ('admin') { <app-admin-panel /> }
  @case ('manager') { <app-manager-panel /> }
  @default { <app-viewer-panel /> }
}

@defer (on viewport) {
  <ejs-chart [dataSource]="chartData()" />
} @placeholder {
  <ejs-skeleton height="300px" />
}
```

**❌ Never use old syntax:**
```html
<!-- Forbidden -->
*ngIf="condition"
*ngFor="let item of items"
*ngSwitch / *ngSwitchCase
```

**Binding rules:**
- `[property]="expression"` for all dynamic values — never HTML attributes for dynamic binding.
- `(event)="handler($event)"` for all event binding.
- `[(ngModel)]` only for simple two-way binding — prefer reactive forms + signals.
- No inline expressions with side effects in templates.
- No method calls in templates that recompute on every change detection — use `computed()` instead.

