### F. SCSS Rules

All styling follows the Khwarizmi token system. See `tokens.rules.mdc` and `colors.rules.mdc` for the full token reference.

**Component SCSS structure:**
```scss
// feature.component.scss

// 1. Host-level layout
:host {
  display: block;
  container-type: inline-size;
}

// 2. Component root — BEM block
.feature {
  padding: var(--spacing-md);        // 16px
  background: var(--color-sf-surface);

  // 3. Elements — BEM __element
  &__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--spacing-md);
    padding-block-end: var(--spacing-md);
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-sf-outline-variant);
  }

  &__content {
    padding-block-start: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  &__footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    gap: var(--spacing-sm);
    padding-block-start: var(--spacing-md);
  }

  // 4. Modifiers — BEM --modifier
  &--compact {
    padding: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
}

// 5. Syncfusion overrides — always scoped to :host
:host ::ng-deep {
  .e-grid .e-headercell {
    background: var(--color-sf-surface-variant);
  }
}

// 6. Responsive — use container queries over media queries when possible
@container (max-width: 600px) {
  .feature {
    padding: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
}
```

**Forbidden in SCSS:**
```scss
// ❌ Hardcoded values
color: #6750A4;
padding: 16px;
font-size: 14px;

// ❌ Non-token spacing
margin: 10px;
gap: 15px;

// ❌ Inline styles anywhere
// <div style="color: red">

// ❌ Global ::ng-deep without :host scope
::ng-deep .e-grid { }   // pollutes other components
```

**RTL-safe CSS:**
- Use logical properties: `padding-inline-start` not `padding-left`, `margin-block-end` not `margin-bottom`.
- Use `inset-inline-start` not `left` for positioned elements.
- These automatically flip in RTL — Syncfusion's `enableRtl(true)` handles component internals.

