### H. Dependency Injection Rules

```typescript
// ✅ Always inject() — not constructor injection
export class FeatureComponent {
  private readonly featureService = inject(FeatureService);
  private readonly router = inject(Router);
  private readonly destroyRef = inject(DestroyRef);
}

// ❌ Never constructor injection
export class FeatureComponent {
  constructor(private featureService: FeatureService) {} // forbidden
}
```

**takeUntilDestroyed for RxJS subscriptions:**
```typescript
import { takeUntilDestroyed } from '@angular/core/rxjs-interop';

export class FeatureComponent {
  private readonly destroyRef = inject(DestroyRef);

  ngOnInit(): void {
    this.service.data$
      .pipe(takeUntilDestroyed(this.destroyRef))
      .subscribe(data => this.items.set(data));
  }
}
```

---

### I. Routing Rules

```typescript
// app.routes.ts — always lazy-loaded feature routes
export const routes: Routes = [
  {
    path: 'users',
    loadComponent: () =>
      import('./features/users/users.component').then(m => m.UsersComponent),
  },
  {
    path: 'users/:id',
    loadComponent: () =>
      import('./features/users/user-detail/user-detail.component')
        .then(m => m.UserDetailComponent),
  },
];
```

- Always lazy-load feature components via `loadComponent`.
- No eager-loaded feature routes.
- Route guards as functional guards (`CanActivateFn`) — not class-based guards.

---

### J. Do / Don't Summary

**Do:**
- ✅ Standalone components only — `standalone: true` always
- ✅ `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` always
- ✅ Signals for all local UI state
- ✅ `inject()` for all dependency injection
- ✅ New control flow: `@if`, `@for`, `@switch`, `@defer`
- ✅ Strongly typed interfaces — never `any` or `object`
- ✅ Logical CSS properties for RTL safety
- ✅ CSS custom properties (tokens) for all SCSS values
- ✅ Lazy-loaded routes only

**Don't:**
- ❌ `any` type — ever
- ❌ `*ngIf`, `*ngFor`, `*ngSwitch` — use new control flow
- ❌ Constructor injection — use `inject()`
- ❌ NgModules
- ❌ Inline styles
- ❌ Business logic in components — belongs in services
- ❌ Hardcoded SCSS values — use tokens
- ❌ Global `::ng-deep` without `:host` scope
- ❌ Method calls in templates that recalculate on every CD cycle
- ❌ Eager-loaded feature routes
